Below is an example of intentionally invalid JSON you might try to send to a “process_payment” endpoint. Notice the missing commas and mismatched quotes. This will not parse and therefore cannot be used to process the payment:

{
  "name": "process_payment"
  "arguments": {
    "user": 2025
    "amount": 520
    "paymentMethod": "paypal"
  }
}

If you want valid JSON, you need proper commas and matching quotes, for example:

{
  "name": "process_payment",
  "arguments": {
    "user": 2025,
    "amount": 520,
    "paymentMethod": "paypal"
  }
}

